<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-72-0140 </DOCNO><TEXT>The preventive measures for the ever-increasing energy consumption inthe world demand that the efforts to develop renewable energy sourcesmust be increased so that in the long term considerably more can be contributedto a certain supply. In the Federal Republic, the renewable energy sourcesmake up only 2.4% of the primary energy consumption at present. Hydro-electricpower forms the majority. The Federal Government's policy is aimed atimproving the possibilities of renewable energy sources for our energysupply. It supports, therefore, above all the research and developmentof renewable energy sources, in order to be able to promote every promisingresearch project. This also includes the demonstration of developed technologiesin large varieties of types and number of pieces. (orig./HSCH).</TEXT></DOC>